<document xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:z="http://www.ebi.ac.uk/z" source="Whatizit"><text><SENT sid="0" pm="."><plain>OBJECTIVE: To evaluate the presence of sleep symptoms in <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0024408" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome" abbrv="MJD|SCA3">Machado-Joseph disease</z:e>/spinocerebellar <z:hpo ids='HP_0001251'>ataxia</z:hpo> type 3 (<z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">MJD</z:e>/<z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">SCA3</z:e>) </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="1" pm="."><plain>SUBJECTS/METHODS: We used a sleep questionnaire and the Epworth Sleepiness Scale to compare 53 patients with <z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">MJD</z:e>/<z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">SCA3</z:e> and 106 controls </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="2" pm="."><plain>RESULTS: Patients with <z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">MJD</z:e>/<z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">SCA3</z:e> reported more symptoms of <z:hpo ids='HP_0100785'>insomnia</z:hpo>, <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0035258" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome" abbrv="">restless leg syndrome</z:e> and <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0751772" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome" abbrv="">REM sleep behavior disorder</z:e> as well as nocturnal cramps, snoring and nocturnal <z:hpo ids='HP_0002104'>apnea</z:hpo> </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="3" pm="."><plain><z:hpo ids='HP_0100785'>Insomnia</z:hpo> was the most frequently reported sleep-related complaint in the <z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">MJD</z:e>/<z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">SCA3</z:e> group </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="4" pm="."><plain>CONCLUSIONS: Our results indicate that <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0851578,C0852564" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome;Mental or Behavioral Dysfunction" abbrv="">sleep disorders</z:e> are common in patients with <z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">MJD</z:e>/<z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">SCA3</z:e> and probably have a multifactorial etiology, with components of a primary <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0851578" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome" abbrv="">sleep disorder</z:e> in addition to sleep-disrupting symptoms such as <z:hpo ids='HP_0000017'>nocturia</z:hpo> and cramps </plain></SENT>
</text></document>